1. Voltage dividers scale 5V input to 2.5V (safe for 3.3V ADC)
2. BAT85 diodes clamp voltage spikes to 3.7V max (100% safe)
3. 100nF smoothing caps are OPTIONAL (filter cable noise)
5. BAT85 cathode (banded end) connects to 3.3V rail
6. Current limiting resistors for LEDs (1k-330 ohm typical)
